    • Method Detail

      • calculateMatch

        public double calculateMatch(java.lang.String comparison)
        Takes a String and scores it with a double from 0 to 1 based on how well it satisfies the term's requirements. For StringArraySchoolSearchTerm, the method interprets the given String as an array with elements delineated by a colon (':'), e.g., "Planes:Trains:Automobiles", "Lions:Tigers:Bears:Oh my", etc. The result is a fractional value: (number of matching Strings in comparison)/(total number of Strings in value array).
        Specified by:
        calculateMatch in class SchoolSearchTerm
        Parameters:
        comparison - the value to be compared as a String
        Returns:
        a score as a double from 0 to 1

      • setValue

        public void setValue(java.lang.String value)
        Sets the value of the term using the String provided. The term's value type is based on the type of the subclass. Also sets included to true. For StringArraySchoolSearchTerm, the method interprets the given String as an array with elements delineated by a colon (':'), e.g., "Planes:Trains:Automobiles", "Lions:Tigers:Bears:Oh my", etc.
        Specified by:
